				"id": "ALAS2023-2024-756",
				"title": "Amazon Linux 2023 - ALAS2023-2024-756: Important priority package update for xorg-x11-server",
				"description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2023 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2024-9632:\n\tA flaw was found in the X.org server. Due to improperly tracked allocation size in _XkbSetCompatMap, a local attacker may be able to trigger a buffer overflow condition via a specially crafted payload, leading to denial of service or local privilege escalation in distributions where the X.org server is run with root privileges.\n",
